White House Press Secretary Sean Spicer begins the briefing by discussing President Trump's speech to Congress the previous night. He describes it as an optimistic, forward-looking message of unity and strength. Spicer mentions that the President is holding meetings with White House staff and congressional leaders to drive the goals outlined in his speech. He also mentions that Judge Neil Gorsuch will be meeting with senators and that the President will be traveling to Hampton Roads and Orlando in the coming days. Spicer then takes questions from reporters on a range of topics including the lunch with Republican leadership, the stock market, healthcare, infrastructure, immigration, and foreign policy.